In the days preceding November 14, Oakland Police delivered 'notices of violations' were delivered to Frank Ogawa plaza. In the early hours of November 14, approximately 700-1000 police were mobilized. Supporters began arriving, and union members organized a picket line. Police initially made about 20 arrests of the camp's Interfaith Ministry who remained in the camp. Afterwards, police demolished the camp.
A citizen-journalist on the scene reported that some of the the men clad in police riot gear lacked any badges and would not provide badge numbers when questioned. <ref>[http://www.ustream.tv/occupyoakland OakFoSho]<!-- Better source needed for long term--></ref>
